Description: In this prequel story, a group of Titan–worshipping cultists open the gates and a baby is the only survivor when a Titan inevitably attacks.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN: BEFORE THE FALL, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama, Ryo Suzukaze and Satoshi Shiki
Contributor: by Hajime Isayama, Ryo Suzukaze and Satoshi Shiki

Description: Is this the end of humanity? It sure looks that way when what is left of mankind must go into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: Mankind has gone into hiding to escape the giant humanoids known as the Titans. In this volume, the Titans attack, but one of them goes rogue.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 2
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: The son of a notorious gangster gets caught in a love triangle with his childhood sweetheart and the daughter of his father’s rival.
Title: NISEKOI: FALSE LOVE, VOL. 2
Author: Naoshi Komi

Description: Set in the same universe as “Negima!,” this series follows Touta, the grandson of Negi Springfield, who becomes a vampire after being mortally wounded.
Title: UQ HOLDER, VOL. 1
Author: Ken Akamatsu

Description: The 104th Training Corps stop for a much–needed respite in Utgard Castle, but their plans to rest are foiled when they discover that the Titans are now attacking at night.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN, VOL. 10
Author: Hajime Isayama

Description: Alice must make a choice once and for all between her two eligible suitors: Peter White and Elliot March.
Title: ALICE IN THE COUNTRY OF CLOVER: MARCH HARE
Author: QuinRose and Soyogo Iwaki

Description: This spin-off series features the middle school adventures of Eren, Mikasa and the rest of the “Attack On Titan” cast.
Title: ATTACK ON TITAN: JUNIOR HIGH, VOL. 1
Author: Hajime Isayama and Saki Nakagawa
Contributor: by Hajime Isayama and Saki Nakagawa

Description: Set in 18th century Europe, this series follows a group of demon hunters known as the Ciste Vihad.
Title: MARCH STORY, VOL. 5
Author: Kim Hyung-min and Yang kyung-il
Contributor: by Kim Hyung-min and Yang kyung-il

Description: Rin Okumura joined an exorcist academy to learn how to control his demonic powers, but will his newfound knowledge ultimately help or hurt him?
Title: BLUE EXORCIST, VOL. 11
Author: Kazue Kato
